## Amendment (post-rebase, kelowna workspace)
User asked to test the integration; a scratch demo (examples/googleAdkDemo.ts,
untracked) was created in the kelowna workspace, which then appeared in every
stack branch's working tree and looked like it was being added by multiple PRs.
User directive: keep the demo in examples/, added once in the relevant PR.
Resolution: deleted the scratch file and folded its deltas into this commit's
canonical examples/googleAdkAgent.ts:
- Env var doc fix: header said GOOGLE_API_KEY, but @google/adk 1.2.0 reads only
  GOOGLE_GENAI_API_KEY || GEMINI_API_KEY (dist/cjs/models/google_llm.js:282 in
  1.2.0; error message at google_llm.js:69 confirms). GOOGLE_API_KEY is never
  consulted.
- Added run command and expected-trace shape (invocation -> invoke_agent ->
  call_llm/execute_tool) to the header so testers know what to verify.
Offline smoke test (no keys) confirmed the CJS require hook patches Runner and
self-registers WeaveAdkPlugin ("Plugin 'weave' registered."); the model call
then fails without GEMINI_API_KEY, which is how the env-var bug was found.
